---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Housing Assistance Eligibility"
  description="Learn about eligibility for Section 8, rental assistance, public housing, and other housing programs in the Bay Area."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav class="mb-6 text-sm" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/eligibility" class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >Eligibility Guides</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="text-neutral-400">/</li>
            <li class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">Housing Assistance</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          Housing Assistance Programs
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-8">
          California and Bay Area agencies offer programs to help with rent, find affordable
          housing, and prevent homelessness.
        </p>

        <!-- Legal Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only and is not legal
            or professional advice. Eligibility requirements may vary by program, county, and individual
            circumstances. Additional requirements may apply beyond what is listed here. To determine
            your actual eligibility, please apply directly to the relevant program or consult with a housing
            counselor. Information is subject to change without notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Section 8 / Housing Choice Voucher -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Section 8 / Housing Choice Voucher (HCV)
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Federal rental assistance that helps pay for private rental housing. You find your own
            housing; the voucher pays a portion of your rent directly to the landlord.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Income Limits (2026 Estimates)
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mb-3">
              Based on Area Median Income (AMI). Limits vary by county - these are approximate for
              the Bay Area.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Extremely Low Income (30% AMI):</strong> ~$36,550 for 1 person, ~$52,200 for
                family of 4
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Very Low Income (50% AMI):</strong> ~$60,900 for 1 person, ~$87,000 for family
                of 4
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Low Income (80% AMI):</strong> ~$97,450 for 1 person, ~$139,200 for family of
                4
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Priority is typically given to extremely low and very low income applicants.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Basic Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Meet income limits for your household size and county</li>
              <li>• Be a U.S. citizen or eligible immigrant</li>
              <li>• Pass background check (requirements vary by housing authority)</li>
              <li>• Not owe money to any housing authority</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>Important:</strong> Most Bay Area waitlists are extremely long (often 5-10+ years)
              and may be closed. Contact your local housing authority to check current waitlist status.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• Apply directly with your county's housing authority when waitlist opens</li>
            <li>• You can apply to multiple housing authorities</li>
            <li>• Keep your contact information updated on all applications</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Emergency Rental Assistance -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Emergency Rental Assistance
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Short-term help paying rent and utilities for people facing housing instability.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Common Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Income typically below 50-80% AMI</li>
              <li>• Experiencing financial hardship or housing instability</li>
              <li>• At risk of homelessness or eviction</li>
              <li>• Not receiving other rental assistance for the same period</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What's Covered</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• Past-due rent (back rent)</li>
            <li>• Future rent (typically 1-3 months)</li>
            <li>• Utility bills (electricity, gas, water)</li>
            <li>• Some programs cover moving costs or security deposits</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Where to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• Contact your county's housing or social services department</li>
            <li>• Community-based organizations and nonprofits</li>
            <li>• 211 hotline can connect you to local resources</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Public Housing -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Public Housing</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Government-owned housing developments with below-market rent based on your income
            (typically 30% of adjusted income).
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Eligibility</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Income limits similar to Section 8 (based on AMI)</li>
              <li>• U.S. citizen or eligible immigrant status</li>
              <li>• Background check</li>
              <li>• References from previous landlords may be required</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>Note:</strong> Public housing availability is limited in the Bay Area. Wait times
              can be several years.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Below Market Rate / Affordable Housing -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Below Market Rate (BMR) / Affordable Housing
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Apartments and homes offered at reduced prices, typically required by cities as part of
            new development. Includes rentals and some ownership opportunities.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Income Limits</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Varies by program: typically 50-120% AMI</li>
              <li>• Some units for very low income (30-50% AMI)</li>
              <li>• Some units for moderate income (80-120% AMI)</li>
              <li>• Must meet both minimum and maximum income limits</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>San Francisco:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://housing.sfgov.org"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >DAHLIA Housing Portal</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• Other counties: Check city housing departments or search for BMR programs</li>
            <li>• Most programs use lottery systems when units become available</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- First-Time Homebuyer Programs -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            First-Time Homebuyer Assistance
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Down payment assistance and favorable loan terms for first-time buyers (or those who
            haven't owned in 3+ years).
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">CalHFA Programs</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>MyHome:</strong> Down payment assistance up to 3.5% of purchase price
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>CalHFA Dream For All:</strong> Shared appreciation loans (when available)
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>CalPLUS/CalHFA Conventional:</strong> First mortgages with down payment help
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">General Requirements</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• First-time homebuyer (haven't owned in past 3 years)</li>
            <li>• Income limits (vary by county and household size)</li>
            <li>• Complete homebuyer education course</li>
            <li>• Meet credit and debt-to-income requirements</li>
            <li>• Home must be primary residence</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • Visit <a
                href="https://www.calhfa.ca.gov"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">CalHFA.ca.gov</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• Work with a CalHFA-approved lender</li>
            <li>• Complete required homebuyer education</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Homeless Services -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Homeless & Housing Crisis Services
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Immediate help for people experiencing homelessness or facing imminent housing loss.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Coordinated Entry</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              The system that assesses housing needs and connects people to available housing
              resources.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Call 211 to connect to your county's system</li>
              <li>• Complete assessment to determine housing priority</li>
              <li>• No documentation required for initial contact</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Emergency Shelters</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Typically first-come, first-served</li>
              <li>• Some require referral from Coordinated Entry</li>
              <li>• Navigation Centers offer additional services</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Get Help Now</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• <strong>Dial 211</strong> for housing resources in any Bay Area county</li>
            <li>• <strong>SF:</strong> SF-311 or HSH hotline</li>
            <li>• Visit local shelters or navigation centers directly</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Bay Area Housing Authorities -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Bay Area Housing Authorities
          </h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">San Francisco</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                SF Housing Authority<br />
                <a
                  href="https://sfha.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">sfha.org</a
                ><br />
                415-715-3200
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Alameda County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Alameda County Housing Authority<br />
                <a
                  href="https://haca.net"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">haca.net</a
                ><br />
                510-727-8511
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Santa Clara County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Santa Clara County Housing Authority<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.scchousingauthority.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                  >scchousingauthority.org</a
                ><br />
                408-275-8770
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Contra Costa County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Contra Costa County Housing Authority<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.contracostahousing.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                  >contracostahousing.org</a
                ><br />
                925-957-8000
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">San Mateo County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Housing Authority of San Mateo County<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.smchousing.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">smchousing.org</a
                ><br />
                650-802-3300
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Marin County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Marin Housing Authority<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.marinhousing.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">marinhousing.org</a
                ><br />
                415-491-2525
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Final Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Important Notice:</strong> The information on this page is for general guidance only.
            Program requirements, income limits, and availability change frequently. This is not a guarantee
            of eligibility or benefits. The only way to determine if you qualify is to apply directly
            to the relevant program. We recommend contacting a HUD-approved housing counselor for personalized
            assistance. Find one at <a
              href="https://www.hud.gov/findacounselor"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
              >hud.gov/findacounselor</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Back Link -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <a href="/eligibility" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg
              class="w-4 h-4 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
            </svg>
            Back to Eligibility Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
